    "body": "```\r\n[09:55:00] | <IceReaper> Regarding #15797 Any idea how to implement the same with FreeActor ?\r\n```\r\n\r\nIMO the best approach for both this and map spawning would be to implement a `GrantConditionWhenProduced` trait that grants a condition on an actor when it is produced through a specific production type (using a `ProductionTypeInit` that is added to the actor via the `DoProduction` init dict).  This condition then becomes a prereq for playing the voice, and all these other cases default to not playing it."
